UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 AN ACT relating to veteran entrepreneurs.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 12 OF KRS CHAPTER
4 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Office" means the Office of Entrepreneurship and Innovation;
7 (b) "Secretary" means the secretary of the Cabinet for Economic Development;
8 (c) "Veteran" means any person who:
9 1. Served in the United States Armed Forces, Reserves, or National
10 Guard and was separated or released therefrom with an honorable
11 discharge, discharge under honorable conditions, or general
12 discharge under honorable conditions; or
13 2. Currently serves in the United States Armed Forces, Reserves, or
14 National Guard; and
15 (d) "Veteran entrepreneurs" means veterans who start or own one (1) or more
16 small businesses.
17 (2) The Veteran Entrepreneur Program is established within the Office of
18 Entrepreneurship and Innovation to provide assistance to veteran entrepreneurs
19 in the Commonwealth.
20 (3) The Veteran Entrepreneur Program shall provide assistance to veteran
21 entrepreneurs by:
22 (a) Performing outreach functions to improve veteran entrepreneurs'
23 awareness of available federal and state benefits and services;
24 (b) Assessing the need for benefits and services among veteran entrepreneurs;
25 (c) Reviewing and researching programs, projects, and initiatives designed to
26 address the needs of veteran entrepreneurs and collaborating with federal,
27 state, and private agencies that provide services to veteran entrepreneurs to
Page 1 of 6
