UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 allow veterans to make use of those services;
2 (d) Evaluating semiannually the effectiveness of the office's efforts to assist
3 veteran entrepreneurs and making appropriate recommendations to the
4 executive director of the office to improve services and assistance provided
5 to those veterans; and
6 (e) Providing information about opportunities for veteran entrepreneurs in the
7 office's collaborative network of businesses and organizations.
8 (4) The secretary shall appoint a program coordinator to administer the program and
9 provide facilities as appropriate in support of the program to the extent funding is
10 available for that purpose.
11 (5) The office may promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS
12 Chapter 13A to effectuate this section.
13 (6) The program shall consult with the United States Department of Veterans Affairs
14 and the United States Small Business Administration in developing procedures
15 under this section to ensure the services provided by this program do not
16 duplicate services provided through the United States Department of Veterans
17 Affairs or the United States Small Business Administration.
18 (7) The office shall establish any additional qualifications necessary for applicants of
19 the program.
20 Section 2. KRS 154.12-277 is amended to read as follows:
21 (1) There is created in the Cabinet for Economic Development the Office of
22 Entrepreneurship and Innovation. The office shall be headed by an executive
23 director appointed by the secretary pursuant to KRS 154.10-050. The office shall be
24 responsible for various forms of entrepreneurship and innovation assistance,
25 including but not limited to providing customer service and project management
26 services to[with] small, [and ]minority, and veteran entrepreneur-owned
27 businesses, assisting export development, administering the innovation assistance
Page 2 of 6
XXXX 11/6/2025 9:08 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 set forth in KRS 154.12-278, introducing entrepreneurs to individual investors and
2 to investment capital firms interested in start-up and early-stage financing, and
3 collecting, summarizing, and disseminating information helpful to businesses,
4 including information on market research, federal, state, and local minority business
5 programs, government procurement opportunities, and the availability of
6 managerial assistance.
7 (2) The office shall include the Commission on Small Business Innovation and
8 Advocacy established in KRS 11.200.
9 Section 3. KRS 154.12-278 is amended to read as follows:
10 (1) As used in this section, "cluster" and "knowledge-based"[ shall] have the same
11 meaning as in KRS 164.6011.
12 (2) The Office of Entrepreneurship and Innovation shall:
13 (a) Implement the Kentucky Innovation and Commercialization Center Program
14 as set forth in KRS 154.12-300 to 154.12-310;
15 (b) Implement and support the Veteran Entrepreneur Program as set forth in
16 Section 1 of this Act;
17 (c) Monitor the return on investments and effectiveness of the Kentucky
18 Innovation Act initiatives as set forth in the Strategic Plan for the New
19 Economy and prepare an annual report by November 1 of each year. The
20 report shall be available on the Cabinet for Economic Development web page
21 as required by KRS 154.12-2035;
22 (d)[(c)] Oversee the modernization initiative in KRS 154.12-274;
23 (e)[(d)] Assist the cabinet in the recruitment of research and development
24 companies;
25 (f)[(e)] Assist the cabinet in the attraction of high-technology research and
26 development centers;
27 (g)[(f)] Support growth and creation of knowledge-based, innovative
Page 3 of 6
XXXX 11/6/2025 9:08 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 companies;
2 (h)[(g)] Build the infrastructure for innovative businesses and promote networks
3 of technology-driven clusters and research intensive industries;
4 (i)[(h)] Administer the high-tech construction pool and the high-tech investment
5 pool;
6 (j)[(i)] Recommend projects to the Kentucky Economic Development Finance
7 Authority for funding through the high-tech construction pool and high-tech
8 investment pool; and
9 (k)[(j)] Review and approve the annual plan which details the annual allocation
10 of funds from the Science and Technology Funding Program. As used in this
11 paragraph, the Science and Technology Funding Program means the
12 Kentucky enterprise fund, the Rural Innovation Program, the Kentucky
13 Commercialization Program, The Regional Technology
14 Corporations/Innovation and Commercialization Center Satellites, the
15 Experimental Program to Stimulate Competitive Research/Kentucky Science
16 and Engineering Foundation, Small Business Innovation Research and Small
17 Business Technology Transfer grants, and other government grant programs
18 and funding programs as determined by the executive director of the Office of
19 Entrepreneurship and Innovation.
20 (3) The high-tech construction pool shall be used for projects with a special emphasis
21 on the creation of high-technology jobs and knowledge-based companies. The
22 executive director, in administering the high-tech construction pool, shall
23 recommend distribution of funds and projects to the Kentucky Economic
24 Development Finance Authority for its approval. The executive director shall
25 recommend any designated amount of pool funds to be set aside for any match
26 requirements. Any funds used for matching purposes may include public and
27 private funds.
