UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 (4) The high-tech investment pool shall be used to build and promote technology-
2 driven industries and research-intensive industries, as well as their related suppliers,
3 with the goal of creating clusters of innovation-driven industries in Kentucky. The
4 executive director, in administering the high-tech investment pool, shall be
5 authorized to recommend funds to be used to support loans and grants, or to secure
6 an equity or related position.
7 (5) The Kentucky Economic Development Finance Authority shall ensure in their
8 approval of funding of projects that the highest priority is given to knowledge-based
9 companies in fulfillment of the purposes and intentions of the purposes of this
10 section.
11 Section 4. KRS 154.12-330 is amended to read as follows:
12 (1) The Kentucky Economic Development Finance Authority is hereby authorized to
13 develop and fund a small business loan program to assist new or existing small
14 businesses operating in the Commonwealth. The authority may lend up to one
15 hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) to any eligible small business for acquisition,
16 construction, expansion, working capital, or any other business expense the
17 authority deems reasonable to approve.
18 (2) The authority shall determine the terms, conditions, and requirements for loans
19 issued under this section and Section 1 of this Act, including collateral
20 requirements when deemed reasonable and appropriate. Recognizing that small
21 businesses, while essential for the economic vitality of the Commonwealth, may
22 have difficulty obtaining conventional loans, the authority may provide terms that
23 are more lenient, high-risk, less secure, or otherwise less stringent than industry
24 standards.
25 (3) To be eligible for a loan under this section, a small business shall be engaged in
26 manufacturing, agribusiness, or service or technology, shall not be engaged
27 primarily in retail, and shall commit to creating and maintaining at least one (1)
Page 5 of 6
XXXX 11/6/2025 9:08 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 103
1 new full-time job above the number existing on the date of application.
2 (4) The authority shall make reasonable efforts to direct at least seven percent (7%)
3 of the small business loan program funds each year to Kentucky-based, veteran
4 entrepreneurs provided that the authority receives qualified applications
5 requesting at least seven percent (7%) of the small business loan program funds.
6 The authority shall develop the criteria to evaluate the applications giving a
7 preference to Kentucky-based companies as defined in KRS 164.6011 that:
8 (a) Were started by one (1) or more veteran entrepreneurs;
9 (b) Are veteran-owned businesses as defined in KRS 14A.1-070; or
10 (c) Employ veterans at a rate of no less than twenty-five percent (25%) of their
11 total employees.
